**[1865, 04-14] Ms.B.1.6.10.24**

May Jr. to RDW

Still talks about how disappointing it was that the British turned
against the North, which “has caused an alienation between this country
& {u}those classes in England{/u} (numerous, wealthy, & influential)
whose sympathies and aid have been so abundant and so powerful,
{u}for{/u} the Rebellion & {u}against{/u} out Country. … This is the day
of the {u}Raising of the Old Flag{/u} on Fort Sumter! Only think of the
fact that Garrison and Geo. Thompson have gone thither, by invitation of
Secretary Stanton of the War Department—{u}the Nation’s Guests{/u}. We
hardly comprehend such changes.”


